File: Chairman of African Rainbow Minerals Patrice Motsepe addresses the Co-Chairs press conference on the second day of the World Economic Forum meeting on Africa, entitled, "Then and now: Reimagining Africa's Future" in Cape Town on June 4, 2015. JOHANNESBURG - Businessman Patrice Motsepe has pledged a billion rand to help combat COVID-19 in South Africa. Motsepe held a media briefing together with their business partners, including Sanlam, African Rainbow Capital as well as African Rainbow Minerals. READ: Motsepe donates R100m for job creation The Motsepe Foundation will also be giving R5-million to help university students affected by the shutdown. Over a thousand cases of COVID-19 have been reported in the country, and the government expects the number to grow in the coming days. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.